      },
      "lineNbr": 97,
      "author": {
        "id": 5395
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-10-11T20:22:23Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not a huge fan of loading everything from scratch every failure - this smells of a cascading failure. (If there are n new digest failures, we trigger m*n+n^2/2 rows read)\n\nIf you want to do something like this, see fs_expstore which uses QuerySnapshots to do an incremental approach (e.g. write to firestore and then get told about new updates from the snapshots)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 97,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 97,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "a31cd16a956ac92170b6b20157286dcb3ffa7192",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
